loom-name: Unmodified SARS and nonSARS coronavirus S and N proteins
loom-description:
Request from Vinay Mahajan at MGH: Nanoluciferase fusion plasmids for LIPS  serological assays.
Contains unmodified SARS coronavirus spike and nucleocapsid proteins and nonSARS nucleocapsids (human codon optimized and native). N-terminally tagged variants. Copied from design 1059 with kozak added.

loom-name: Protein Engineering library of SARS-CoV-2 spike ectodomain prefusion conformation (1120)
loom-description: Full-length ectodomain Protein Engineering libraries of SARS-CoV-2 spike (S) protein. Notes from the template: This version of S features an abrogated furin cleavage site and two proline mutations to stabilize the prefusion conformation. The design follows from Walls et al. Cell (2020) and includes a T6 trimerization domain, TEV cleavage site, and 8xHis tag. pcDNA3.1 vector for use in transient transfection expression systems.
